verbose_text: In order to assess the specificity of the process leading to high levels of ROS in irradiated cells, a co-culture (1:1 cell ratio) of CD20 expressing Burkitt lymphoma B cells and K562 erythromyeloblastoid leukemia cells that do not express CD20, was incubated with anti-CD20-coated gold nanoparticles and irradiated by eight pulses.
